TwitterCamp is an Adobe Flex-application to graphically display tweets around a certain subject.
A certain programming-experience is required to customize, no settings are provided.

The app is built according to the principles of Model-View-Controller.
The model consists out of a TwitterSearch-instance, that will automatically refresh its 
tweets and notify any listening objects.
